A study on malaria conducted in Namsang Circle of Tirap District (Arunachal Pradesh) during April-October 1986 revealed that the malaria incidence due to Plasmodium falciparum was considerably high. RII level of chloroquine resistance was also found among the P. falciparum cases studied by WHo in-vivo test. In entomological survey, Anopheles maculatus was collected more than other 10 anopheline species encountered. A. minimus was detected and incriminated as a vector species.